to respond to that violence with violence.

674
00:39:37,667 --> 00:39:39,965
When I think of
all the people that I've lost,

675
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:46,476
I remember the choices that I was forced
to make in light of those tragedies.

676
00:39:50,471 --> 00:39:51,973
Some choices were easy.

677
00:39:54,309 --> 00:39:57,313
But the important choices,
the choices that were worth making,

678
00:39:57,478 --> 00:39:58,525
they were hard.

679
00:39:59,856 --> 00:40:01,984
And hard choices require bravery.

680
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:06,530
Fortunately, we live
in the home of the brave.

681
00:40:07,155 --> 00:40:09,408
We don't run from hard choices.

682
00:40:09,574 --> 00:40:13,169
We rise up and we face tomorrow together.

683
00:40:15,622 --> 00:40:19,468
This afternoon, Councilwoman Pollard and I

684
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:25,341
met with the city council to pass
the Star City Firearms Freedom Act,

685
00:40:25,548 --> 00:40:28,176
<i>a policy that respects our freedom</i>

686
00:40:30,386 --> 00:40:31,683
and our lives.

687
00:40:35,058 --> 00:40:36,731
It shows that we can do both.

688
00:40:41,731 --> 00:40:44,530
And now we just have to be
brave enough to do it.

